Charmm-gui parameters for modifications
https://www.charmm-gui.org/

# Input files MOD1
final_mod1.pdb
MOD1.mol2

#Input files MOD2
final_mod2.pdb
MOD2.mol2

#Uploading
Protein/Membrane System > Download Source: OPM , PDB Format: PDB

#Model/Chain Selection
Select both chain A and UNK (in both cases UNK was the modified ligand)

#PDB Manipulation options
Terminal group patching: PROA > ACE, CT3

#Disulfide Bonds
CYS262-CYS259
CYS159-CYS71
CYS74-CYS146
CYS77-CYS166

#Orientation 
Align the First Principal Axis Along Z

#Area Calculation Options
Generate Pore Water and Measure Pore Size > Using protein geometry

#System size determination
Box Tyoe: Rectangular
Water thickness: 12
Length of XY based on: Ratios of lipud components
Length of X and Y: 90 #bigger box to avoid periodic boundary condition effects
Lipid Type: POPC 1:1

#Input Generation Options:
GROMACS, NAMD

#Equilibration Options:
Generate grid information for PME FFT automatically, NPT ensemble
